```js
async function reconcileBatch(batch, next) {
  try {
    const rows = await db.fetchRows(batch);
    const results = apply_rules(rows);
    await db.save(results);
    emit_metrics(results);
  } catch (err) {
    next(err);
  }
}
```

Changes:
- `reconcileBatch` now `async`
- `db.fetchRows` → `await`
- `db.save` → `await`
- `apply_rules`, `emit_metrics` remain synchronous calls
- Any db error caught, forwarded via `next(err)`
- Order preserved: `load_batch` > `db.fetchRows` > `apply_rules` > `db.save` > `emit_metrics`
- Batch passed as argument, serves as `load_batch` entry point
- Minimal surface change, no structural rework

